laboratory_examinations.findings: The tip of the appendix appears dilated, measuring 8.5 mm. There is stranding about the appendix as well as the mucosal hyperenhancement. No adjacent fluid collection or foci of free air. The liver enhances homogeneously. No focal lesion identified. Gallbladder demonstrates radiopaque stones without evidence of cholecystitis. The pancreas is without ductal dilatation. Kidneys present symmetric nephrograms and excretion of contrast. No hydronephrosis or perinephric stranding.
Bilirubin level: 14.0 mg/dL (Reference range: 6.0 - 20.0 mg/dL); within normal range.
